  "description": {
    "en": "Recognizable by their leathery armor shell, they are excellent diggers that feed mainly on insects.",
    "zh": "以其坚韧的铠甲外壳而容易辨认，它们是出色的挖掘者，主要以昆虫为食。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "The nine-banded armadillo is about the size of a large cat, weighing 2.5 to 6.5 kilograms. Its body is covered in bony plates that form a hard, armor-like shell with nine movable bands around its middle. It has a long, pointed snout, big ears, and sharp claws made for digging.",
      "zh": "九带犰狳大约有一只大猫那么大，体重2.5到6.5公斤。它的身体覆盖着骨质甲片，形成坚硬的铠甲状外壳，中间有九条可活动的带。它有长长的尖鼻子、大耳朵和用于挖掘的锋利爪子。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Nine-banded armadillos are mostly nocturnal and eat ants, beetles, and other insects by digging them out of the ground with their strong claws. An amazing fact is that a mother armadillo almost always gives birth to four identical quadruplets! When startled, they can jump straight up in the air.",
      "zh": "九带犰狳大多在夜间活动，用强壮的爪子从地下挖出蚂蚁、甲虫和其他昆虫来吃。一个惊人的事实是，犰狳妈妈几乎总是一胎生下四个一模一样的四胞胎！受到惊吓时，它们会直直地跳到空中。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Nine-banded armadillos prefer warm, rainy areas with soft soil for digging, such as forests, scrublands, and grasslands. They are found across the southern United States, Mexico, Central America, and much of South America. They have been steadily expanding their range northward in the United States.",
      "zh": "九带犰狳喜欢温暖多雨、土壤松软适合挖掘的地方，如森林、灌木丛和草原。它们分布在美国南部、墨西哥、中美洲和南美洲大部分地区。在美国，它们的分布范围一直在稳步向北扩展。"
    }
  },
